<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Entitlements for the native Teleprompter macOS app — applies to TestFlight /
  Mac App Store (Release) archive builds.

  com.apple.security.app-sandbox: REQUIRED by App Store Connect for Mac App Store
  and TestFlight distribution (ASC error 90296 if absent). This file is picked up
  only by the Release archive path (scripts/ios.sh archive). Local ad-hoc macOS
  smoke builds (TP_PLATFORM=macos scripts/ios.sh build/smoke) pass
  CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS="" at xcodebuild time, which CLEARS this file entirely
  (scripts/ios.sh lines 509 and 1790) — so adding sandbox here does NOT affect the
  local macOS smoke path.

  com.apple.security.network.client: required inside the sandbox so the app can
  open outbound network connections (WebSocket to the relay server). Without this,
  a sandboxed build would be unable to connect to any relay URL and would be
  completely non-functional.

  keychain-access-groups: required for the Keychain to be usable on macOS. The
  Keychain API (SecItemAdd etc.) requires this entitlement; without it access is
  restricted to items created without an access group. The group uses the bundle
  id so it is stable across signed and ad-hoc builds.

  APNs (aps-environment) is intentionally OMITTED here, mirroring the iOS
  entitlements file. The full macOS push *software* path is wired
  (NSApplication.registerForRemoteNotifications → TeleprompterMacAppDelegate →
  PushTokenStore → relay.push.register); the ONLY remaining piece is this
  entitlement, which requires a Developer ID / provisioning profile and cannot be
  ad-hoc signed ("-"). Adding it here would break the native macOS smoke build
  (CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY="-"). Add a separate signed-build entitlements file with
  <key>aps-environment</key><string>development|production</string> when a
  real-Mac push build ships.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- Required by ASC (error 90296) for Mac App Store / TestFlight submission. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>
    <!-- Required inside the sandbox to open outbound WebSocket connections to the relay. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
    <key>keychain-access-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>$(AppIdentifierPrefix)dev.tpmt.app</string>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
